[English]
# Terms of reference Call PyBAQ Lightning Talks 2020

### Description:

In December, we will be holding an event that seeks that many of you can tell us about your ideas related to Python, soft skills or programming in general through lightning talks.

We will use the Pecha Kucha methodology, in which each speaker will have the opportunity to make their presentation using the 20x20 format, that is, 20 slides with 20 seconds of explanation for each one.

**More information:**
http://blogs.brighton.ac.uk/jamesbry/2016/05/02/how-to-create-the-perfect-pecha-kucha/

### Event dates:

**- Call of proposals:** October 26 - November 15
During this stage we will be receiving all your [applications here](https://forms.gle/QGQZf5LnRozDHNLT6) to read  all those great ideas you have to share with us. Keep in mind that we are open to talks at all levels and to support you in case you need help in structuring the content.

**- Evaluation of proposals:** November 16 - November 18
Here we will be evaluating each of the applications to define the pre-selected ones.

**- Publication of pre-selected:** November 19
We will be announcing the list of 13 people pre-selected candidates to the next phase.

**- Reception of presentations:** November 19 - November 29
The pre-selected must prepare their presentations for the event and will send it to the PyBAQ team for the selection of the best talks that will be at the event.

**- Final evaluation:** November 30 - December 3
The PyBAQ team will review the submitted submissions and define the best ones according to the evaluation rubric. The talks with the best scores will be presented at the event.

**- Publication of final selection:** December 4
At this point, we will be confirming to those selected the necessary logistics details. Likewise, a member of the PyBAQ team will contact you to confirm that you have received the information and that you are still willing to participate.

**Event:** December 10
The great day to share with the community all the topics and talks prepared by the selected people.


